## Task: Frontend WebSocket Integration
**Sprint:** 2 (Week 3-4) | **Priority:** P0 | **Type:** Frontend Integration
**Assignee Role:** Frontend Dev
**Depends On:** SP02-T03

---

### Step 1: Write Tests FIRST
```typescript
describe('useWebSocket hook', () => {
  it('connects with JWT token on mount');
  it('disconnects on unmount');
  it('auto-reconnects with exponential backoff');
  it('shows connection status: connected/reconnecting/disconnected');
  it('dispatches events to correct subscribers');
  it('buffers events during disconnect, replays on reconnect');
});

describe('useRealtimeQuery hook', () => {
  it('invalidates React Query cache on matching WebSocket event');
  it('does not invalidate on non-matching event type');
});

describe('WebSocket Provider', () => {
  it('provides connection state to children');
  it('filters events by tenant context');
});
```

### Step 2: Development Prompt
```
Create React hooks for WebSocket integration:
- useWebSocket(): connect/disconnect lifecycle, auto-reconnect, status indicator
- useRealtimeSubscription(eventType): subscribe to specific events, auto-unsubscribe
- useRealtimeQuery(queryKey, eventType): auto-invalidate React Query on WS event
- WebSocketProvider: context provider wrapping the app
- ConnectionStatusBadge: visual indicator (green dot/yellow/red)

Use native WebSocket API. No heavy libraries.
Store connection in React context. TypeScript with proper event typing.
```

### Definition of Done
- [ ] All hook unit tests passing
- [ ] WebSocket connects on app mount, reconnects on disconnect
- [ ] Dashboard data refreshes when WS events arrive
- [ ] Connection indicator visible in top bar

## Task: Listing Management UI
**Sprint:** 4 (Week 7-8) | **Priority:** P0 | **Type:** Frontend
**Assignee Role:** Frontend Dev
**Depends On:** SP02-T02, SP04-T01

---

### Step 1: Mockup (Stitch)
```
Design a product listing management page for an Amazon seller dashboard:
1. Catalog table view: columns for image thumbnail, ASIN, title (truncated), quality score
   (color-coded 0-100), Buy Box %, price, BSR, status badge. Sortable, filterable, searchable.
   'Optimize with AI' button per row.
2. AI Listing Editor: split-screen — left panel with generation inputs (product name, features,
   keywords, brand voice selector), right panel with Amazon-style preview of generated listing.
   Character counts, keyword highlighting, diff view (current vs proposed), Approve & Publish button.
Dark navy sidebar, data-heavy layout, professional SaaS style.
```

### Step 2: Write Tests FIRST
```typescript
ListingCatalog:
  it('renders listing table with all columns');
  it('sorts by quality score on column click');
  it('filters by status dropdown');
  it('searches by ASIN or title');
  it('shows quality score color: red 0-40, amber 41-70, green 71-100');
  it('opens AI editor on Optimize button click');
  it('shows loading skeleton while fetching');
  it('shows empty state for no listings');

ListingEditor:
  it('renders input fields for generation');
  it('shows loading animation during AI generation');
  it('displays generated content in preview panel');
  it('shows character count with warning near limit');
  it('highlights target keywords in generated text');
  it('shows diff view comparing current vs proposed');
  it('calls approve API on Approve button click');
  it('shows publishing status indicator');
```

### Step 3: Frontend Generation
**Lovable:** Full page prototype with mock data for stakeholder review
**v0:** Individual production components — ListingTable, QualityBadge, SEOScoreBar, DiffViewer

### Step 4: Integration
```typescript
// E2E Test
test('generate and approve listing flow', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/listings');
  await page.click('[data-testid="optimize-btn-0"]');
  await page.fill('[name="productName"]', 'Wireless Earbuds');
  await page.fill('[name="keywords"]', 'wireless earbuds, bluetooth');
  await page.click('button:has-text("Generate")');
  await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="preview-title"]')).not.toBeEmpty();
  await page.click('button:has-text("Approve")');
  await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="status"]')).toHaveText(/submitted/i);
});
```

### Definition of Done
- [ ] Catalog table renders with sorting, filtering, search
- [ ] AI editor generates listing content via API
- [ ] Diff view shows current vs proposed
- [ ] Approve flow saves to agent_actions and triggers SP-API submission
- [ ] All unit + integration + E2E tests passing
